        "timestamp": 1756414071
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>1B: what you have is fine. I'll note that <code>grind</code> works to prove that <code>have</code> though. <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span> I understand this may not be conducive to learning necessarily.</p>",
        "id": 536681554,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1756414185
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>2C: You could do simply: <code>rw [← sb_right_inv f g xA1, ← sb_right_inv f g xA2, hxeq]</code> in place of:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">have</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxeq'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">invFun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x₁</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">invFun</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x₂</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">by</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">hxeq</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">sb_right_inv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xA1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sb_right_inv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xA2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxeq'</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">exact</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxeq'</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Or alternatively, you could do:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">replace</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxeq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">congr</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">$</span><span class=\"n\">hxeq</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">rw</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">sb_right_inv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xA1</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">sb_right_inv</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">f</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">g</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">xA2</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">at</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">hxeq</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>assuming the <code>congr</code> term elaborator is available at this point in MIL. Otherwise you could do: <code>replace hxeq := congrArg g hxeq</code>.</p>",
